tech.mcprison.prison.internal

Interface CommandSender

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Player

    public interface CommandSender
    Represents any entity that may send commands and receive output.
    Since:
    API 1.0

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Returns the name of the command sender.

      • dispatchCommand

        void dispatchCommand(java.lang.String command)
        Force a commandSender to send a command

      • doesSupportColors

        boolean doesSupportColors()
        Returns true if the command sender can show colors to the viewer. This is not always the case, especially when using command blocks and online consoles.

      • hasPermission

        boolean hasPermission(java.lang.String perm)
        Returns true if the command sender has access to the permission specified.
        Parameters:
        perm - The permission to check.

      • sendMessage

        void sendMessage(java.lang.String message)
        Sends a message to the command sender. If the command sender supports colors, color codes will automatically be parsed and shown. If not, color codes will simply be stripped from the message.
        Parameters:
        message - The message to send. May include color codes, amp-prefixed.

      • sendMessage

        void sendMessage(java.lang.String[] messages)
        Sends multiple messages to the command sender. Each message will be shown on its own line.
        Parameters:
        messages - The array containing each message.
        See Also:
        sendMessage(String)

      • sendRaw

        void sendRaw(java.lang.String json)
        Send a raw JSON message to the sender.
        Parameters:
        json - The JSON message. Must be in proper format.
